  journal       = {EDUCACAO E SOCIEDADE},
  abstract      = {A scoping review about teacher occupational well-being and high-stakes accountability is presented, based on 32 publications searched in SciELO, Scopus, and WOS (2010-2020). The main results indicate that: 1) the publications emanate mainly from the United States and England; 2) the topic has been studied through five theoretical approaches, with explanatory and comprehensive preeminence of those that integrate contributions from Education Sciences and Occupational Health; and 3) the high-stakes accountability affects five working conditions of teachers, deteriorating their occupational well-being and inducing stress and burnout. At the end, epistemological and theoretical implications are discussed, and proposing projections for a research problem still under construction.},
