  title         = {INTERLINKING FEMINISM AND ANTI-RACISM IN SANTIAGO DE CHILE (2010–2020): CHALLENGES FOR COALITION BUILDING},
  year          = {2023},
  journal       = {Dialogo andino},
  abstract      = {This article analyses, from an intersectional feminist perspective, a series of interviews with feminist and anti-racist activists regarding their experiences and memories of participation in the feminism of the last decade in Chile. Particularly, the focus is on the processes of coalition-building and knotting between feminism and anti-racism. As a theoretical framework, we will review key discussions on intersectionality, memory, and feminist coalition building. We carry out a contextualization of feminist activism in Chile in the period 2010–2020 with a focus on intersectional alliances, accounting for the complexity of local feminist demands and struggles. The analysis discusses differences, tensions, and challenges present in the experiences of coalition generation, to contribute to the visibility and articulation of anti-racist feminist demands and struggles, highlighting the knowledge and reflections that the activists carry out starting from their political practices.},
